---
alwaysApply: true
---
At the start of every conversation, task, or agent session, always read AI_MEMORY.md before doing substantive work.

Use AI_MEMORY.md as the project’s durable memory for context, progress, decisions, verification, and meaningful completed work.

If meaningful project changes happen, update AI_MEMORY.md every time, using the format inside the Write All Meaningful Changes Here section.

Meaningful changes include code changes, doc changes, skill changes, rule changes, database/setup changes, important bug fixes, important verification results, durable decisions, confirmed project facts, or important user constraints.

Keep memory updates short, factual, and useful.

Never store secrets, passwords, tokens, API keys, private keys, full database URLs, or private company/customer data.

After updating memory, tell the user:

Memory updated: <timestamp>

Make sure the timestamp matches the Last updated field in AI_MEMORY.md.